\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Pre-convergence safety window $W(r)$. Replica~A receives the \texttt  {Revoke} and immediately stops accepting $U$'s operations. Replica~B, partitioned from~A, continues accepting $U$'s operations under stale evidence. After anti-entropy delivers the revocation, both replicas replay the merged log deterministically; the deny-wins gate skips $U$'s post-revocation operations, and both converge to the same state~$s^\star $. The safety window $W(r) \leq \Delta _{\mathrm  {partition}} + \Delta _{\mathrm  {propagation}}$ is bounded under the finite partition assumption.}}{11}{figure.58}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:safety-window-paperC}{{6}{11}{Pre-convergence safety window $W(r)$. Replica~A receives the \texttt {Revoke} and immediately stops accepting $U$'s operations. Replica~B, partitioned from~A, continues accepting $U$'s operations under stale evidence. After anti-entropy delivers the revocation, both replicas replay the merged log deterministically; the deny-wins gate skips $U$'s post-revocation operations, and both converge to the same state~$s^\star $. The safety window $W(r) \leq \Delta _{\mathrm {partition}} + \Delta _{\mathrm {propagation}}$ is bounded under the finite partition assumption}{figure.58}{}}
\newlabel{fig:safety-window-paperC@cref}{{[figure][6][]6}{[1][10][]11}}
