\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Partition-heal semantics and the finite pre-convergence safety window $W(r)$. During $W(r)$, a replica that has not yet received \texttt  {Revoke(U)} may tentatively accept writes under stale evidence. After anti-entropy, all replicas replay the same union log in the same order; the revoke closes $U$'s epoch, post-revoke writes are skipped, and the final digital state converges. The guarantee is about the reconciled digital state, not rollback of physical-world effects already triggered during the partition.}}{13}{figure.74}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:partition-heal-paperC}{{7}{13}{Partition-heal semantics and the finite pre-convergence safety window $W(r)$. During $W(r)$, a replica that has not yet received \texttt {Revoke(U)} may tentatively accept writes under stale evidence. After anti-entropy, all replicas replay the same union log in the same order; the revoke closes $U$'s epoch, post-revoke writes are skipped, and the final digital state converges. The guarantee is about the reconciled digital state, not rollback of physical-world effects already triggered during the partition}{figure.74}{}}
\newlabel{fig:partition-heal-paperC@cref}{{[figure][7][]7}{[1][12][]13}}
